National Security Advisor Susan Rice met with Foreign Secretary Philip Hammond of the United Kingdom to discuss various issues. They emphasized their commitment to achieving a comprehensive deal regarding the ongoing P5+1 nuclear negotiations with Iran. They also agreed that a military-only approach in Yemen would lead to further suffering and destabilization in the region, and that a negotiated political solution is the best outcome. Additionally, they expressed their support for the United Nations' efforts to form a unity government and resolve the conflict in Libya.